Ingest Knowledge Article Data from Salesforce CRM

In Data Cloud, you can use the Knowledge Article data kit to ingest knowledge article data from your CRM org. The data kit includes default mappings to the relevant data model objects (DMOs) in Data Cloud.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: All Editions supported by Data Cloud. See Data Cloud edition availability.


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To ingest Knowledge Article data:	

One of these permission sets:

Data Cloud Admin
Data Cloud Marketing Admin
Data Cloud Data Aware Specialist

Knowledge objects were added in version 3.0 of the Service Cloud data bundle. Ensure your Service Cloud data bundle is version 3.0 or higher.

Knowledge Articles contain both structured and unstructured data that is useful for grounding service replies and prompts that are contextualized for a customer’s use case. For example, the Knowledge Article Version object includes these fields that should be indexed for search:

Custom text fields: any rich text fields (131K limit) that hold unstructured data
Name: The name or title of the Knowledge Article
Description: The description or summary of the Knowledge Article
In Data Cloud, go to the Data Streams tab, and click New.
Select the Salesforce CRM data source, and click Next.
Select a Salesforce org, and click Next. If you have only one Salesforce org connected to Data Cloud, it’s selected by default.
Select Knowledge, and click Next.
Review the fields for the four Knowledge objects that are included in your data stream. The number of fields available for the object is in parentheses.
Standard fields from the objects in your data kit are automatically mapped to the relevant data model objects in Data Cloud. However, you must manually map any custom fields.
Deselect any fields not required for your data stream, and click Next.
Review the new data streams and objects to be deployed from the data stream kit, and click Deploy.

After successful deployment of the data stream, click Data Lake Objects and verify the objects are listed:

Knowledge_ka_<YOUR_ORG_ID>
Knowledge_kav_<YOUR_ORG_ID>
LinkedArticle_<YOUR_ORG_ID>
CaseArticle_<YOUR_ORG_ID>
